Because of how well red kidney beans hold their shape during cooking they're perfect for simmered dishes like this one. This veggie curry is filled with protein, fibre and of course, plenty of flavour.

== Curry ==

Add @cold salted water{300%ml} to a medium #pot with a tight-fitting #lid.

Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pot from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Trim half the @cucumber{1/2}(trimmed and quartered lengthways, then chopped widthways into small pieces).

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Quarter the @lemon{1/2}(quartered).

Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%pack} in a #sieve. Mash half with a #fork.

Place a large #pot over medium-high heat with @butter{1%tbsp}.

When hot, add half the chopped onion and fry for ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @North Indian style spice mix{1%sachet} and fry for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @chopped tomato with onion & garlic{1%pack} and beans (both mashed and whole).

Cover and simmer for ~{10-12%minutes}. Add the @garam masala{1%sachet} when the curry has ~{2%minutes} left to simmer.

== Cucumber and Coriander Salad ==

Meanwhile, in a #bowl mix the chopped cucumber, remaining chopped onion and half the coriander.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @lemon juice{remaining}(squeezed).

== Finishing ==

Stir half the @creme fraiche{125%g} into the curry and allow to warm through.

Season to taste with salt, pepper and @sugar{to taste}.

Add a splash of @water{} to loosen the curry if required.

Divide the curry between #bowls{} with spoonfuls of fluffy rice.

Squeeze over remaining lemon juice to taste.

Top with remaining coriander and creme fraiche.

Serve with cucumber salad alongside.